The paper deals with deep neural networks and their optimization through weight pruning techniques. Specifically, it focuses on combining two types of structured weight pruning (filter and column prune) using the ADMM algorithm. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves optimization algorithms and techniques, which could place it in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also deals with data structures and compression, which could make it relevant to the data structures (cs.DS) sub-category.
